1. using alien thread for non-trivial business logic.
- practice of executing complex or important business logic on threads that are not dedicated to the current operation
or context.

*** Alien Threads
An "alien thread" is any thread that originates outside the current context or control.
These threads could be part of a thread pool managed by a framework, library, or some external system.
They are not owned or managed directly by the business logic that is being executed.

*** Non-Trivial Business Logic
"Non-trivial business logic" refers to complex, important, or critical operations within your application.
This might include operations like processing transactions, handling critical data transformations, or performing intricate calculations.